reviews.review:
I was promised hope and happiness and a satisfying end. What I got was a convoluted mess that was lacking in emotional resonance. I left feeling cheated and disheartened. I was willing to forgive almost every error this film made until the final minutes. The omission of a major character, and not even showing anyone else giving him a second thought was insulting not only to him but to every other beloved character that had made a sacrifice in his behalf. 
I have the highest respect for the actors involved. They made me truly love their characters. They were the heart and soul of these movies. And they deserved better. ALL of them. JJ Abrams and whoever else was calling the shots on the ending of this film should be ashamed of themselves.

Overall felt waaaay too rushed. It was too concerned with retconning what was done in the two previous films that we didn't get the satisfying ending that we wanted. Seriously, the ending was terrible and did not leave me feeling hopeful when it was over. There was never a moment to breath or cry - which can be good to some but bad for others (bad to me). Like other star wars films, the action was there and was fun to watch. I wish there were more movies coming, as the film didn't feel complete.

We went to see Star Wars in IMAX and loved it. I feel they tied everything up very well and greatly enjoyed how they paid homage to the previous films. I will also admit that the ending made me tear up a little because it was such a perfect way to end it
Sad to see this franchise end with such an inane plot.

I enjoyed Episode 9 for the most part. The ending was weird though, like they cut the scenes all to hell at the last minute. Finn's arc wasn't resolved either and that was disappointing. I wish Ben and Rey had ended up together and both alive; killing Ben to redeem him felt like a cop out.
very solid end to the saga!

There a lot wrong with this movie, including some plot and character inconsistencies but ultimately there's a lot more The Rise of Skywalker gets right! It seems critics and audiences can't agree on what makes a great Star Wars movie. To me it's the way the story flows, how the mythos are defined, and the action; this movie sticks the landing on the last two.
Really delivered an ending to the saga with many details from the past movies wrapped up
